text: Budj Bim, also called Mount Eccles, is a dormant volcano near Macarthur in southwestern Victoria, Australia. It is in the Budj Bim National Park. "Budj Bim" is a Gunditjmara name meaning "High Head". The volcano is around high. It became a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2019. ==References== Category:World Heritage Sites in Australia Category:Volcanoes of Australia Category:Geography of Victoria, Australia
